partial_orders.reason: Both edits perform an identical textual substitution pattern: adding ', pool_size=(8, 8)' to _cfg() calls that have 'input_size=(3, 256, 256)'. This is a bulk uniform substitution targeting the same type of syntactic construct (_cfg function calls) with the exact same before→after pattern. The edits are clearly part of a single, contiguous refactor operation to add pool_size parameters to multiple model configurations. Either edit can be staged first, and after making either, the other would be the natural next step in completing this uniform substitution pattern.
